HEADWORD: needlewood
<hw>nee"dle*wood`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A large bushy shrub
(<spn>Hakea leucoptera</spn>) of central and eastern Australia, with
pungent pointed leaves and creamy white flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> needle wood, <spn>Hakea leucoptera</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
